frameDefinitions: A Figure is located essentially at the same location as a Ground, which is viewed as point-like, or having no important internal or external structure.
A Figure is located relative to a Ground location.
This frame contains nouns denoting Quantities of a specified Entity and their numerical Values.
A Location is filled or covered with the Theme.
The Fastener is an artifact created to close a Container (e.g. coat, jar).
frameExamples: His heart attack was caused by a high cholesterol <t>level</t>.
The waters of the bay <t>teemed</t> with fish.
The door <t>seal</t> prevented air from getting in and the kids' screams from getting out.
listRoleDefinitions: The <fen>Ground</fen> serves as a basis for describing the location of the <fen>Figure</fen>.
The <fen>Figure</fen> is perceived as located relative to a certain <fen>Ground</fen> location. The <fen>Figure</fen> can be an entity or an event.
The period of time during which the locative relation between <fen>Figure</fen> and <fen>Ground</fen> obtains.
The <fen>Ground</fen> serves as a basis for describing the location of the <fen>Figure</fen>.
The <fen>Figure</fen> is perceived as located relative to a certain <fen>Ground</fen> location. The figure can be an entity or an event.
The region within which a <fen>Figure</fen> might be found.  This role is exclusive of <fen>Figure</fen>, and is a reconstrual that is not possible with verb lexical units.
The period of time during which the locative relation between <fen>Figure</fen> and <fen>Ground</fen> obtains.
<fen>Entity</fen> identifies the concept or substance being quantified by a <fen>Quantity</fen>.
<fen>Value</fen> identifies the numerical amount of the <fen>Entity</fen>.
The <fen>Theme</fen> covers or fills the <fen>Location</fen>.  This role most frequently occurs in a PP Complement headed by with or in.
<fen>Location</fen> is the object or area that the <fen>Theme</fen> fills or covers.  This frame element generally occurs as the External Argument.
The period of time during which the the Abounding_with event occurs.
This role identifies the item that is closed with the <fen>Fastener</fen>.
The artifact created to close a <fen>Container</fen>.
This role identifies the active zone of the container where the <fen>Fastener</fen> is located.
listRoleExamples: He was at my shop <fex>on Friday</fex>.
<fex><t>Next to</t> the kitchen</fex> is the best place to locate your garage .
Their <fex><t>level</t></fex> of productivity decreased with each hour of overtime worked.
He wrote me a check in the amount <fex>of $500</fex>.
The waters of the bay teemed <fex>with fish</fex>.
<fex>The walls</fex> crawled with nanite surveillance probes.
On Friday night, many men will simply elect to remove their tie and unbutton their top <fex>shirt</fex> button.
Man, I have just bought the exact same belt <fex><t>buckle</t></fex> and it won't open.
We couldn't close the <fex>tent flap</fex> zipper and a lot of flies came in .
